The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Friday, July 01, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Midnapore, June 30: A man found guilty of murder told a court here today that he preferred death sentence to life imprisonment. 

 An additional sessions judge, Mir Dara Shoko, sentenced Gunadhar Mahato, 40, to death by hanging. He killed his brothers wife with an axe during a feud in the family at Amgachhia, Kharagpur, about 130 km from Calcutta. Asked why he sought death, Mahato simply said: It is my wish. 

 Calcutta: The deadline for Great Eastern Hotel employees to pick up early retirement scheme forms expired on Thursday with 421 out of 426 having collected them. Till evening, 413 employees had also submitted their papers.

 Burdwan: A teacher has been arrested from Narja village in Bhatar, about 130 km from Calcutta, for allegedly mole-sting a Class III student. 




